## V. Equivariant Filter
## A. Error Dynamics

Fix the origin state $\xi^{0}=\left(\boldsymbol{I}_{5 \times 5}, \boldsymbol{O}_{9 \times 9}, \boldsymbol{I}_{4 \times 4}\right)$. For current state $\xi \in \mathcal{M}$, define $e=\phi_{\dot{X}^{-1}}(\xi)=\phi_{X \dot{X}^{-1}}\left(\xi^{0}\right)=\phi_{E}\left(\xi^{0}\right) \in$ $\mathcal{M}$ to represent the error on $\mathcal{M}$, where $E=X \dot{X}^{-1}$ is right invariant error on $G$ [26]. Choose a local coordinate map $\varphi$ : $U \rightarrow \mathbb{R}^{9} \oplus \mathbb{R}^{9} \oplus \mathbb{R}^{6}$ at the origin $\xi^{0}, \varphi$ can be taken as

$$
\varphi(e)=\log _{G} \circ\left(\phi^{\left(\xi^{0}\right)}\right)^{-1}(e)
$$

Let $\varepsilon=\varphi(e) \in \mathbb{R}^{24}$. The linear error $\varepsilon$ satisfies

$$
\begin{aligned}
& \dot{\varepsilon} \approx \boldsymbol{F} \varepsilon+\boldsymbol{B} \boldsymbol{n} \\
& \boldsymbol{F}=\left(d \varphi\right)_{\xi^{(0)}} \circ\left(d \phi^{\left(\xi^{0}\right)}\right)_{j} \circ\left(d \Lambda_{\boldsymbol{n}}\right)_{\xi^{0}} \circ\left(d \varphi^{-1}\right)_{\mathbf{0}}
\end{aligned}
$$

where $\boldsymbol{n}$ denotes the Gaussian noise. The state matrix $\boldsymbol{F}$ is

$$
\boldsymbol{F}=\left[\begin{array}{lll}
\boldsymbol{F}_{T} & \boldsymbol{I}_{9 \times 9} & \boldsymbol{O}_{9 \times 6} \\
\boldsymbol{O}_{9 \times 9} & \boldsymbol{F}_{b} & \boldsymbol{O}_{9 \times 6} \\
\boldsymbol{F}_{K T} & \boldsymbol{F}_{K b} & \boldsymbol{F}_{K}
\end{array}\right] \in \mathbb{R}^{24 \times 24}
$$

where

$$
\begin{aligned}
\boldsymbol{F}_{T} & =\left[\begin{array}{lll}
\boldsymbol{g}^{w^{\wedge}} & & \\
& \boldsymbol{I}_{3 \times 3} & \end{array}\right], \boldsymbol{F}_{b}=\operatorname{ad}_{\Lambda_{1}\left(\xi^{0}, \boldsymbol{u}^{0}\right)}^{\vee} \in \mathbb{R}^{9 \times 9} \\
\boldsymbol{F}_{K b} & =\left[\begin{array}{lll}
\boldsymbol{I}_{3 \times 3} & \boldsymbol{O}_{3 \times 3} & \boldsymbol{O}_{3 \times 3} \\
\boldsymbol{O}_{3 \times 3} & \boldsymbol{O}_{3 \times 3} & \boldsymbol{I}_{3 \times 3}
\end{array}\right] \in \mathbb{R}^{6 \times 9} \\
\boldsymbol{F}_{K T} & =\left(\boldsymbol{I}_{6 \times 6}-\operatorname{ad}_{\Gamma\left(\Lambda_{1}\left(\xi^{0}, \boldsymbol{u}^{0}\right)\right)}^{\vee}\right)\left[\begin{array}{c}
\boldsymbol{I}_{3 \times 3}
\end{array}\right] \in \mathbb{R}^{6 \times 9} \\
\boldsymbol{F}_{K} & =\operatorname{ad}_{\Gamma\left(\Lambda\left(\xi^{0}, \boldsymbol{u}^{0}\right)\right)}^{\vee} \in \mathbb{R}^{6 \times 6}
\end{aligned}
$$

The letters with hat in them represent the estimated value of that state and $\boldsymbol{I}$ represents the identity matrix. The derivations of the state matrix $\boldsymbol{F}$ and the input matrix $\boldsymbol{B}$ are privided in the supplementary material [22].
